SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1207
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to recognize Cathy Hamsley, Administrator of
Elections for the Robertson County Election
Commission, on the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Cathy Hamsley of Robertson County is one such estimable person, who
evinces the greatest integrity and probity in all her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, after nearly four decades of distinguished service to the Robertson County
Election Commission, including the last twenty-three as Administrator of Elections, Ms. Hamsley
is taking a much-deserved retirement; and
WHEREAS, she began her distinguished career with the Robertson County Election
Commission in 1988 as an office clerk and was appointed Administrator of Elections in 2003;
and
WHEREAS, Cathy Hamsley exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and
community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Hamsley is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service
that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we commend Cathy Hamsley for her honorable and
astute service to the Robertson County Election Commission, extending to her our heartfelt
wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her future
endeavors.
